  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 6d0ab5d8d318a4e42b80d35e7dce2d6c, type: 3}
  m_Name: _Tier1-StartNews-Nafta
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::RevManager.NewsEventData
  Headline: NAFTA privatizes indigenous farmlands
  Body: "IRA imposes sweeping land reforms threatening to displace millions from
    communal edijos. A few of our neighbours have banded together to protect their
    communal land from government take over. Emiliano Zapata fought for the freedom
    of these lands during the revolution and now his legacy is being sold off to
    capitalist pigs. Our people are forced to flee to the cities, with nowhere to
    turn for survival except the factories owned by those same blood-drinking cockroaches.
    We must carry on the legacy of Zapata, bring together people in support of our
    cause, and stand against this pillaging of our rights and dignity.\n\n\u201CThe
    neo-liberal dream of a Mexican countryside without peasants or indigenous peoples
    is nothing but a nightmare and a vain illusion. Mexico cannot exist without Mexican
    peasants and indigenous peoples. Without corn, there is no country.\u201D"
  Image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 0f673f8fdd72744d4a5d48b8ad1ae7ba, type: 3}
  Tone: 3
  OneTimeOnly: 1
